xbrlcore.dimensions
Class SingleDimensionType

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.dimensions.SingleDimensionType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class SingleDimensionType
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

This class encapsulates a dimension and a specific element of that dimension.

If it is an explicit dimension, the element of the dimension is a domain member and therefore a Concept object itself. If it is a typed dimension, it either has no element or this element is of type org.jdom.Element.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
Checks whether two SingleDimensionType objects are equal. If both represent explicit dimensions, this is true if both refer to the same dimension and domain member concept.
If both represent typed dimensions, this is true if both refer to the same dimension concept and if the typed domain member are equal. Currently only simple typed member are supported (no nested elements).

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Returns:
true if both objects are equal, false otherwise.
